	<entry xml:lang="en">
		<title>esp hardware</title>
		<published>2022-12-12T00:00:00+00:00</published>
		<updated>2022-12-12T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
		<link rel="alternate" href="https://aniewoehner.github.io/blog/pages/esphome/esp-hardware/" type="text/html"/>
		<id>https://aniewoehner.github.io/blog/pages/esphome/esp-hardware/</id>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;esp8266 vs esp32
8266 has some advantages using unsecured access point, not going to do that
for secured (WPAx) access point, esp32 has advantage&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESP32 - 2016 - plain - Wi-Fi 4, bt 4.2 &lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESP32-C6 - 2021 - 32-bit RISC-V, 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi 6, Bt (LE) 5, IEEE 802.15.4, nothing found?&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mini and wroom&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESP32-C3 - 2020 - 32-bit RISC-V &amp;lt;160MHz, 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi, Bt (LE) 5, 400 kB SRAM 384 kB ROM, spi&#x2F;qpi, $10 for one&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mini and wroom&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESP32-C2 -  - 32-bit RISC-V &amp;lt;120MHz, 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi, Bt (LE) 5, 272 kB SRAM, 16kB cache, 576 kB ROM, nothing found?&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mini and wroom&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESP32-S3 - 2020 - 32-bit LX7, 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi, Bt (LE) 5, 3 for $20&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mini and wroom&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESP32-S2 - 2019 - 32-bit LX7, 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi, 3 for $15&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mini and solo, wrover and wroom not rec for new design, &lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;supposedly S2 is much more energy efficient, adds a different camera interface&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;S2, C3, S3 have native USB, no need for usb-to-serial chip&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RISC-V are lower cost&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;S3 is like updated ESP32, higher specs&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WROOM - does not use the 2 GPIOs&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
